ecoQuery: https://ecoquery.ecoinvent.org/3.10/cutoff/dataset/1364/documentation

This is a market activity. Each market represents the consumption mix of a product in a given geography, connecting suppliers with consumers of the same product in the same geographical area. Markets group the producers and also the imports of the product (if relevant) within the same geographical area. They also account for transport to the consumer and for the losses during that process, when relevant.;This is the market for  'willow stem cutting, for planting', in the Global geography.;This product is generally considered to be used at the production site.  Therefore, the market does not contain any transport.;This product is a willow stem cutting, that is usedfor plant propagation. It has an average mass of 20g per piece (fresh matter), while the yield is 100,000 stem cuttings per hectare. The process includes machine operations and machinery, storage, end-of -life, land use and  direct field emissions.

This activity starts at the gate of the activities that produce 'willow stem cutting, for planting',  within the geography of Global.

This activity ends with the supply of  willow stem cutting, for planting', to the consumers of this product. Transport or losses are considered irrelevant for this product.
